CHROME OPTIONS - REVISION NOTES

ChromeOptions is a Selenium class used to customize the Chrome browser before launching it.

1. Headless Mode
----------------
options.addArguments("--headless=new");

Purpose:
- Runs the browser without opening the UI.
- Useful in CI/CD pipelines and faster execution.

2. Incognito Mode
-----------------
options.addArguments("--incognito");

Purpose:
- Launches Chrome in Incognito mode.
- No cache, cookies, or browsing history are stored.

3. Accept Insecure SSL Certificates
-----------------------------------
options.setAcceptInsecureCerts(true);

Purpose:
- Bypasses SSL certificate warnings.
- Useful in QA/UAT environments with self-signed certificates.

4. Remove "Chrome is being controlled by automated test software" Message
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
options.setExperimentalOption("excludeSwitches",
        new String[]{"enable-automation"});

Purpose:
- Removes the automation-controlled notification displayed by Chrome.

OTHER COMMONLY USED CHROME OPTIONS
----------------------------------

options.addArguments("--start-maximized");
Purpose:
- Opens browser in maximized mode.

options.addArguments("--disable-notifications");
Purpose:
- Disables browser notifications.

options.addArguments("--disable-popup-blocking");
Purpose:
- Disables popup blocking.

options.addArguments("--guest");
Purpose:
- Opens Chrome in Guest mode.

options.addArguments("--window-size=1920,1080");
Purpose:
- Launches browser with a custom window size.

INTERVIEW DEFINITION
--------------------
ChromeOptions is a Selenium class used to customize the behavior of the Chrome browser
before launching it, such as running in headless mode, incognito mode, handling SSL certificates, disabling notifications, and configuring browser startup settings.